From d2d8eb053b08202a0b922b7306029986e2175815 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Lids Labs <55252374+lidslabs@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Wed, 22 Jul 2026 16:29:04 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 15/15] lidslabs v0.4.0: NVEncC transcode engine for the
 muted-DV fix (LIDSLABS_TRANSCODE_NVENCC)

Gate a DV Profile 7/8.1 HEVC transcode onto rigaya NVEncC when a DV-render-capable
client (LIDSLABS_TRANSCODE_DV_CLIENTS, default moonfin/streamyfin) requests it.
NVEncC decodes+encodes with --dolby-vision-profile 8.1 --dolby-vision-rpu copy so
the dynamic RPU survives in-band, fixing the washed-out picture mpv clients show on
high-mastering-peak P7 titles. NVEncC writes mpegts to a FIFO; ffmpeg stays the
Jellyfin-monitored process, stream-copies the video from the FIFO and transcodes
audio from the source, keeping stdin free for the graceful 'q' stop. NVEncC runs as
a sidecar tracked on the TranscodingJob and killed on stop. HLS and progressive
paths both covered; subtitle burn-in/embed falls through to stock. Fail-open when
the flag is unset.
